# SHA256SUMS — pinned checksums for the flow-server release assets named in RELEASE.
# Format: "<sha256>  <asset>" (sha256sum / shasum -a 256 output), one asset per platform.
# POPULATED WHEN A RELEASE IS CUT: the flow-server-release CI workflow builds each asset and
# emits a SHA256SUMS file as a release artifact; copy its lines below and commit, then the
# launcher (flow-server-mcp) retrieves + verifies instead of falling back to a source build.
# The launcher's parser skips these comment lines and accepts only 64-hex digests, so the
# example/instruction comments are safe to keep above the real entries.
# Asset name: flow-server-<target-triple>[.exe], e.g.
#   flow-server-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu
#   flow-server-aarch64-apple-darwin
#   flow-server-x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe
